      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PLAYA DEL CARMEN (2) went back last start then worked home in good style to finish just 9 metres from the winner in second at Bendigo over 2150m to make it three minor placings in a row. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Meets a comparable field and she can take care of this line-up. BILLY ZIPPIN (11) was out of the money two runs ago then broke and finished fourth last start over 2150m at Bendigo, coming home 15 metres from the winner. Draws out a little on the second line and may need luck at some point. Only needs to get things right to be in contention. BROWN EYED KATE (3) is better than her last-start eighth over 2570m at Ararat. Each-way chance. ALDEBARAN MAVERICK (10) was out of the money two runs ago then broke and finished ninth last start over 2150m at Bendigo, coming home 35 metres from the winner. Won't find this any harder and he can bounce back.",
